(1. Console Overview) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
11.5 TL
0.102 g
54. 706. Td
(The Dispatch Console is the control center for managing active calls-for-service, unit status, and field activity. It) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
11.5 TL
0.102 g
54. 692. Td
(combines a real-time call stack, unit roster, map, and a command line that mirrors traditional CAD radio shorthand.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
11.5 TL
0.102 g
54. 678. Td
(Everything you see updates live across every connected workstation via WebSocket — when another dispatcher) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
11.5 TL
0.102 g
54. 664. Td
(changes a unit's status, your screen reflects it within roughly one second. There is no manual refresh; the) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
11.5 TL
0.102 g
54. 650. Td
(authoritative state lives on the server, and your screen is always rendering the latest snapshot.) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
11.5 TL
0.102 g
54. 632. Td
(The console is designed around one principle: the dispatcher should never have to hunt for information. Everything) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
11.5 TL
0.102 g
54. 618. Td
(an officer might ask you for — nearest unit, premise alerts, outstanding warrants on a subject, priority call count,) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
11.5 TL
0.102 g
54. 604. Td
(beat assignment — should be visible or one hotkey away. If you find yourself clicking through more than two) Tj
ET
BT
/F1 10 Tf
11.5 TL
0.102 g
54. 590. Td
(menus to answer a question, there is almost certainly a command-line shortcut that gets you there instantly.) Tj
ET
